Definition:
	Groups of code which do a single function. Although you can write functions to do multiple things, it is generally frowned upon to define function with multiple uses. Functions are stand-alone in C++.

Syntax:
	Data_type function_name( arguments ) {
		return value;
	}

	you can also declare the function with defining it:

	Data_type function_name( arguments );

Examples:
	int get_number( int arg1, char arg2 );

	...

	int get_number( int arg1, char arg2 ) {

	}
